org.jcvi.jillion.experimental.align

Interface AlnVisitor


  • public interface AlnVisitor
    AlnVisitor is a visitor interface to visit aln formatted data like that produced by multiple sequence alignment programs such as ClustalW.

    Usually .aln files split an alignment into "groups". Each group contains a consecutive block of alignment data for all the input that aligned in that region. Visiting an alignment will therefore require visiting several groups. Sequences may span consecutive groups if the sequence is longer than the group length.

    Author:
    dkatzel

      • visitGroup

        AlnGroupVisitor visitGroup(Set<String> ids,
                           AlnVisitor.AlnVisitorCallback callback)
        Visit the next group. Usually .aln files split an alignment into "groups". Each group contains a consecutive block of alignment data for all the input that aligned in that region. Visiting an alignment will therefore require visiting several groups. Sequences may span consecutive groups if the sequence is longer than the group length.
        Parameters:
        ids - the sequence ids contained in this group; will never be null and should never be empty.
        callback - the AlnVisitor.AlnVisitorCallback for this group; will never be null.
        Returns:
        a AlnGroupVisitor instance to visit this group; or null to skip this group.

      • visitHeader

        void visitHeader(String header)
        Visit the Header of this alignment data.
        Parameters:
        header - a single line that will start with either "CLUSTAL W" or "CLUSTALW" but may have more information than that (including version etc); will never be null or empty.
